<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-420-956  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 420 956.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 7 1990 n366 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>International sales flourish. (sales figures for the first quarterof 1990)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly; Hedlund, Kristen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>US computer vendors have posted sales and revenue figures for thefirst quarter ended Mar 31, 1990 that show the increasingimportance of the international market.andP;  A report by the GartnerGroup Inc shows that strong growth in the international arena iscompensating for the relative flatness of the US market.andP;  Of sixleading vendors analyzed in the report, all reported strong firstquarter sales.andP;  Lotus Development Corp reports international salesup 84 percent (compared with 9.5 percent growth in US sales).andP;  SunMicrosystems Inc had 46 percent growth in international sales andonly 10.6 percent domestic growth.andP;  In addition, SoftwarePublishing experienced 67 percent international growth and CompaqComputer Corp's international sales grew by 56 percent, whileMicrosoft Corp grew by 62 percent and Apple by 27 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gartner Group Inc. (research).andO;Topic:     First QuarterSalesRevenueInternational TradeComputer IndustryVendorsMarket Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   (First quarter international sales figures for six US computercompanies). (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>